keyFacts: The document is a U.S. Customs and Border Protection (CBP) travel record for Ghislaine Maxwell.
It records Maxwell's inbound arrival at Miami International Airport on August 6, 1997, at 15:07 Eastern Time.
The flight was PJ41, seat A520, and the processing result was 'NOT REFERRED', indicating no secondary inspection or referral to another agency.
The report was generated on September 21, 2021, suggesting it was retrieved or produced during the investigation into Maxwell.
The document is marked 'For Official Use Only / Law Enforcement Sensitive'.
